==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Calefacient
<hw>Cal`e*fa"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>calefaciens</ets> p. pr. of <ets>calefacere</ets> to make warm;
<ets>calere</ets> to be warm + <ets>facere</ets> to make.]</ety>
<def>Making warm; heating.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calefacient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Calefacient
<hw>Cal`e*fa"cient</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A substance that excites
warmth in the parts to which it is applied, as mustard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calefaction</ent>⟦br⟧
